    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-23T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-23T01:00:00-05:00" n="278"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3531/895: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-23T02:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 23, 1939—2 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>133. Your 135, August 22. Confirming arrangement made in telephone conversation
                    with Tuck<note n="19" xml:id="d278fn19">S. Pinkney Tuck, Counselor of Embassy in
                        Argentina.</note> notice of intention to negotiate trade agreement will be
                    issued for publication in afternoon papers Wednesday, August 23.<note n="20"
                        xml:id="d278fn20">Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>,
                        August 26, 1939, pp. 166–170.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
